title: Bug 109350 - Output parameter does not display in data set dialog.
OB: When calling a stored procedure from Oracle database and storing the query result in an output parameter as an object, the output parameter does not display in the edit data set dialog.
EB: The output parameter should be displayed in the edit data set dialog.
SR:
Steps to reproduce:
1. Call a stored procedure from Oracle database.
2. Store the query result in an output parameter as an object.
3. Open the edit data set dialog to view the output parameter.
